     .

         Less Fire-Prone Cigarettes
         Archived reports from the Cigarette Safety Act of 984 and the Cigarette
         Safety Act of 1990.  Plus, new results on cigarettes with banded paper.

     .

         Workshop on Fire Testing Measurement Needs
         for U.S. Fire Testing Laboratories
         June 18-19, 2001
         BFRL is organizing a workshop for U.S. fire testing laboratories to
         identify non-proprietary problems common to the community, to
         prioritize them, and to discuss mechanisms for solving them.

     .

         Interflam 2001
         9^th International Fire Science & Engineering Conference
         17^th - 19^th September
         Edinburgh Conference Centre
         Edinburgh, Scotland

         Interflam has grown from being the largest and longest established
         international fire research conference (held every 3 years since 1979)
         into a multifaceted event with the conference at the core of the
         programme...
         More information about Interflam 2001

         Register for the International Conference on Engineered Fire Protection
         Design being held on June 11-15, 2001 in San Francisco, CA.

